   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER FIVE THE CHURCH LIFE IN GOD'S ECONOMY Scripture Reading: Phil 1:20-21a; John 21:15-17; Rev 2:4; Phil 3:12; 1 Cor 1:9; Col 1:12, 18b; 1 Tim 4:6; Eph 4:3-4, 12, 16; 3:8-10, 2; Acts 8:1; 13:1; Rev 1:11; John 17:21-23; Rev 1:12, 20b; 1 Tim 3:15-16; Rom 15:16; 1 Pet 2:5, 9; 1 Cor 4:15; 1 Thes 2:7; 1 Pet 2:2; Heb 10:24-25; 1 Cor 14:1-5, 12, 31, 40; Col 3:10-11 OUTLINE To live and magnify Christ --Phil 1:20-21a: To love and treasure Christ --John 21:15-17; Rev 2:4.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>To pursue and gain Christ --Phil 3:12.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>To enjoy and partake of Christ --1 Cor 1:9; Col 1:12.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>To exalt and minister Christ --Col 1:18b; 1 Tim 4:6.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>To build up the Body of Christ --Eph 4:12: To keep the universal oneness of the Body --Eph 4:3-4.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>By all the members of the Body, perfected in the local churches --Eph 4:12: Either as the joints of the rich supply of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Or as parts of the Body operating in their measure --Eph 4:16.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>With the unsearchable riches of Christ --Eph 3:8-10.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Through the divine dispensing --Eph 3:2.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>To meet as a proper local church --Acts 8:1; 13:1; Rev 1:11: On the genuine ground of the unique oneness of the Body --Eph 4:3-4; John 17:21-23.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>As a local expression of the universal Body of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>As a local golden lampstand --Rev 1:12, 20b.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>As the pillar and base of the truth for the manifestation of God in the flesh --the great mystery of godliness --1 Tim 3:15-16.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Meeting and serving in mutuality according to the God-ordained way: Fulfilling the New Testament gospel priesthood for begetting --Rom 15:16; 1 Pet 2:5, 9; 1 Cor 4:15.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Nourishing and cherishing the new believers in home meetings --John 21:15; 1 Thes 2:7; 1 Pet 2:2.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Perfecting the saints in group meetings that they may be able to do the work of the ministry, that is, to build up the Body of Christ --Eph 4:12; Heb 10:24-25.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Prophesying in the church meetings for the building up of the Body of Christ through the local churches --1 Cor 14:1-5, 12, 31.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Having the adequate and proper leadership for the keeping of a good order 1 Cor 14:40 with the all-inclusive Christ as the center and the processed Triune God as the manifestation --Col 3:10-11; 1 Tim 3:15-16.</S>
   </TEXT>
